# Multi-Agent Research System - Codex Rules

## Project Architecture
- This is an async-capable, multi-agent Python application.
- All agents inherit from `research_agents/agents/base_agent.py`.
- All inter-agent data flows through `research_agents/models/research_state.py`.
- Never use bare dicts where a Pydantic model exists.

## Code Standards
- Python 3.11+, typed wherever practical.
- Pydantic v2 for all data models.
- Loguru for logging.
- External calls go through retry-aware wrappers.
- Keep prompts in `prompts.py`.

## Testing
- Mock Gemini and E2B in unit tests.
- Skip live integration tests by default.

